  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Patients with a cardiac stab wound could be complicated by a posttraumatic acute myocardial
      infarction (PAMI). Traditionally, the investigators can explain it by the occlusion of a
      coronary artery; but the PAMI isnÂ´t constantly related with coronary artery injuries or their
      damage in the cardiac injury repair. The investigators objectives are to know the PAMI
      incidence, make an approximation to PAMI pathophysiology, and propose management strategies.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
